---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Neighbors from "../../../components/Neighbors.astro";
---

<Layout title="Cognitive Architectures" favicon="🏛️">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to reading</a>

    <h1>🏛️ Cognitive Architectures</h1>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 mb-6">Four decades of attempts to build a complete mind. From Minsky's society of agents to Soar's production systems to the transformer stack that accidentally ate the world. Each entry extracts the reusable mechanisms — algorithms that belong in the <a href="https://june.kim/the-parts-bin"><img src="/reading/jk.png" alt="jk" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/>parts bin</a>.</p>

    <!-- SVG: Timeline of architectures -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 480 100" class="w-full max-w-lg" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- Timeline line -->
        <line x1="30" y1="50" x2="450" y2="50" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>

        <!-- Symbolic (blue) -->
        <circle cx="80" cy="50" r="6" fill="#60a5fa" fill-opacity="0.3" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="80" y="30" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="9">1986</text>
        <text x="80" y="75" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="9">Society</text>
        <text x="80" y="86" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="9">of Mind</text>

        <!-- Neural (amber) -->
        <circle cx="240" cy="50" r="6" fill="#f59e0b" fill-opacity="0.3" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="240" y="30" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="9">2017</text>
        <text x="240" y="75" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="9">Attention Is</text>
        <text x="240" y="86" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="9">All You Need</text>

        <!-- Hybrid (green) -->
        <circle cx="340" cy="50" r="6" fill="#34d399" fill-opacity="0.3" stroke="#34d399" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="340" y="30" text-anchor="middle" fill="#34d399" font-size="9">2022</text>
        <text x="340" y="75" text-anchor="middle" fill="#34d399" font-size="9">Soar</text>

        <!-- LLM era (purple) -->
        <circle cx="380" cy="50" r="6" fill="#a78bfa" fill-opacity="0.3" stroke="#a78bfa" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="380" y="30" text-anchor="middle" fill="#a78bfa" font-size="9">2023&#x2192;</text>
        <text x="380" y="75" text-anchor="middle" fill="#a78bfa" font-size="9">LLM</text>
        <text x="380" y="86" text-anchor="middle" fill="#a78bfa" font-size="9">Survey</text>

        <circle cx="440" cy="50" r="6" fill="#a78bfa" fill-opacity="0.3" stroke="#a78bfa" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="440" y="30" text-anchor="middle" fill="#a78bfa" font-size="9">2026</text>
        <text x="440" y="75" text-anchor="middle" fill="#a78bfa" font-size="9">Agent</text>
        <text x="440" y="86" text-anchor="middle" fill="#a78bfa" font-size="9">Stack</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-6" style="display:flex;gap:2em;flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1;min-width:200px;">
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-2">1986</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300" style="margin:0">Agents compose into agencies.<br/>No agent is intelligent.<br/>The society is.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1;min-width:200px;">
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-2">2022</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300" style="margin:0">Four memories. Four learning modules.<br/>One decision cycle.<br/>Forty years of walls.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1;min-width:200px;">
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-2">2017→2026</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300" style="margin:0">Attention is all you need.<br/>Scale is all you need.<br/>Alignment is all you need.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-8">Three traditions. One question: what does a complete cognitive system require? The reading order below goes chronological. The <a href="https://june.kim/the-parts-bin"><img src="/reading/jk.png" alt="jk" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/>parts bin</a> columns show which mechanisms each architecture contributes.</p>

    <hr class="border-zinc-700 mb-8"/>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Papers</h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-700">
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">Work</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">One sentence</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 text-gray-400"></th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/cognitive-architecture/minsky-1986/">Minsky 1986</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Intelligence emerges from vast numbers of mindless agents organized into agencies — no single principle, just diversity</td><td><a href="/reading/cognitive-architecture/minsky-1986/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🏛️</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/cognitive-architecture/vaswani-2017/">Vaswani et al. 2017</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Replace recurrence with self-attention — the architecture that made scale possible</td><td><a href="/reading/cognitive-architecture/vaswani-2017/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🏛️</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/cognitive-architecture/laird-2022/">Laird 2022</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Four memories, four learning modules, one decision cycle — the most complete symbolic architecture ever built</td><td><a href="/reading/cognitive-architecture/laird-2022/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🏛️</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/cognitive-architecture/zhao-2023/">Zhao et al. 2023→2026</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">The full LLM stack: pre-training, alignment, utilization, and evaluation — a living survey</td><td><a href="/reading/cognitive-architecture/zhao-2023/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🏛️</a></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/cognitive-architecture/arunkumar-2026/">Arunkumar et al. 2026</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">The agent stack on top of LLMs: perception, memory, planning, action, tools, and multi-agent coordination</td><td><a href="/reading/cognitive-architecture/arunkumar-2026/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🏛️</a></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <hr class="border-zinc-700 my-8"/>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">What to look for</h2>
    <ul class="text-gray-400 space-y-1 mb-4">
      <li>Which of the six roles does each architecture fill? Which are missing?</li>
      <li>Where does learning happen — and where does it stop?</li>
      <li>What algorithms are portable across architectures?</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-8">📺 Video lectures: <a href="https://ocw.mit.edu/courses/6-868j-the-society-of-mind-fall-2011/">MIT 6.868J: Society of Mind (Minsky)</a> · <a href="https://karpathy.ai/zero-to-hero.html">Karpathy: Neural Networks: Zero to Hero</a></p>

    <Neighbors>
    <ul class="neighbors">
      <li><a href="/reading/cognitive-science/">🧠 Computational Cognitive Science</a></li>
      <li><a href="/reading/natural-breadcrumbs/">🍞 Natural Breadcrumbs</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://june.kim/the-parts-bin"><img src="/reading/jk.png" alt="jk" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/> The Parts Bin</a></li>
    </ul>
    </Neighbors>


  </main>
</Layout>
